    <section id="faq" class="faq section-bg">
      <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">

        <div class="section-title">
          <p>CA Benefits Program Information</p>
        </div>

        <ul class="faq-list" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">

          <li>
            <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" class="collapsed question" href="#faq1">CalWORKS <i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
            <div id="faq1" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
              <p>
                <a href="http://www.benefitscal.org/" target="_blank">CalWORKS</a> is the California extension of TANF, a federal program known as the Temporary Assistance to Needy Families,
                and it provides public assistance and cash to eligible families with children. It is designed to transition families from 
                welfare to work.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq2" class="collapsed question"> Women, Infant, and Children (WIC) <i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
            <div id="faq2" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
              <p>
                The <a href="https://m.wic.ca.gov/" target="_blank">Woman, Infant and Children</a> program provides families with funds to purchase healthy foods from WIC approved
                grocers, supplementary information on how to live a healthy lifestyle, and help in finding healthcare and other
                valuable community services.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq3" class="collapsed question"> Supplemental Security Income<i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
            <div id="faq3" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
              <p>
                The <a href="https://www.ssa.gov/ssi/" target="_blank">Supplemental Security Income</a> provides monthly payments to people who have limited income and few resources,
                primarily those who are disabeled, or over the age of 65. It is administered through Social Security, an insurance program for retirees, those with disabilities, and aged peoples and their families.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq4" class="collapsed question">CalFresh<i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
            <div id="faq4" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
              <p>
                The <a href="http://www.benefitscal.org/" target="_blank">CalFresh Program</a> provides low-income families with funds to purchase food items at eligible grocers. This is primarily 
                meant to be a supplementary tool.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq5" class="collapsed question">MediCal<i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
            <div id="faq5" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
              <p>
                <a href="http://www.benefitscal.org/" target="_blank">MediCal</a> is a Medicaid program in California funded by the Department of Health Care Services that provides healthcare
                services and coverage to low-income families and individuals, including foster children, seniors, pregnant women, and
                people with disabilities. Services include ambulatory patient services, dental care, mental health care, hospitalization, and long-term care.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <div data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#faq6" class="collapsed question">Section 8 <i class="bi bi-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bi bi-chevron-up icon-close"></i></div>
            <div id="faq6" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
              <p>
                <a href="https://www.hud.gov/topics/housing_choice_voucher_program_section_8" target="_blank">Section 8</a> is a rental assistance 
                program managed by the Department of Housing and Urban Development that pays for rent for low-income American households to private landlords. It is a voucher
                program (most households pay up to 30% of their adjusted income, of the gross income minus the deductions for dependents),
                allowing for tenants to look for and move into an approved housing unit.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

        </ul>

      </div>
